- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses queries on finite graphs.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper mentions polynomial-time computable queries.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with relations between nodes in graphs, which could be relevant to certain machine learning applications.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also less likely but possible as the polyadic mu-calculus is a formal language used to express properties of programs.
